From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:27:17 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] skia: bind sample-only AHardwareBuffers as external GL
 textures

Ganesh's GL AHardwareBuffer import always creates the backend texture with
the target implied by the buffer's format, which for the common concrete
formats is GR_GL_TEXTURE_2D. On the Adreno 506 (a5xx, KGSL) this makes the
driver take an upload/detile path when the imported gralloc buffer is only
ever sampled, and that path overruns the buffer: app-drawer icons and other
hardware bitmaps come out corrupted or blank.

Restore the Android-15 behaviour of selecting the target by renderability:
renderable buffers stay GR_GL_TEXTURE_2D (external textures cannot be FBO
attachments), while sample-only buffers are imported as GR_GL_TEXTURE_EXTERNAL
so the driver samples the gralloc allocation directly. Formats that are already
external (e.g. R8G8B8X8) are left untouched, and the renderability check now
runs against the format actually used.
---
 src/gpu/ganesh/gl/AHardwareBufferGL.cpp | 16 ++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/gpu/ganesh/gl/AHardwareBufferGL.cpp b/src/gpu/ganesh/gl/AHardwareBufferGL.cpp
index 361ab66982..0590d4697a 100644
--- a/src/gpu/ganesh/gl/AHardwareBufferGL.cpp
+++ b/src/gpu/ganesh/gl/AHardwareBufferGL.cpp
@@ -248,13 +248,25 @@ GrBackendTexture MakeGLBackendTexture(GrDirectContext* dContext,
         return GrBackendTexture();
     }
 
+    // Select the GL target by renderability (as Android-15 Skia did). Renderable buffers must be
+    // GR_GL_TEXTURE_2D (external textures cannot be FBO attachments). Sample-only buffers are bound
+    // as GR_GL_TEXTURE_EXTERNAL so the GPU driver samples the gralloc buffer directly; binding them
+    // as 2D makes the Adreno driver upload/detile the buffer, and that upload path overruns the
+    // buffer on this device. Only concrete (2D) formats are retargeted; already-external formats
+    // (e.g. R8G8B8X8) are left unchanged.
+    GrBackendFormat effectiveFormat = backendFormat;
+    if (!isRenderable && backendFormat.textureType() == GrTextureType::k2D) {
+        effectiveFormat = GrBackendFormats::MakeGL(GrBackendFormats::AsGLFormatEnum(backendFormat),
+                                                   GR_GL_TEXTURE_EXTERNAL);
+    }
+
     if (isRenderable &&
-        !dContext->priv().caps()->isFormatRenderable(backendFormat, /*sampleCount=*/1)) {
+        !dContext->priv().caps()->isFormatRenderable(effectiveFormat, /*sampleCount=*/1)) {
         return GrBackendTexture();
     }
 
     return make_gl_backend_texture(dContext, hardwareBuffer, width, height, deleteProc,
-                                   updateProc, imageCtx, isProtectedContent, backendFormat);
+                                   updateProc, imageCtx, isProtectedContent, effectiveFormat);
 }
 
 }  // namespace GrAHardwareBufferUtils
